snippet.textDisplay:
My favorite so far has to be the Bod.  Shotgun that has SMG secondary (that I always use for ammo purposes) but still fires multiple rounds counting as one shot. Damage is massive, but the best part is that it counts as every primary weapon type so any perk and any stat buff you use counts towards it no matter what. So if you‚Äôve got a class mod that increases pistol damage by 50% and an enhancement that increases sniper damage by 50% for example, even though the gun is neither of those types it will do +100% damage. 

Plus it talks and periodically gives you encouraging words of affirmation!

snippet.textDisplay:
Barrage is a locked part on Firewerks. Every shield will roll with that. The only part that isn't fixed is the middle one. Stoic is kinda a dead one on the Firewerks, it's good (for other shields), but half the shield's power comes from segments breaking to proc missile swarm, and Stoic Firewerks slow that down. I would recommend farming for 'Encouraging', which gives a 15% chance on kill to spawn extra armor boosters to refill armor segments or 'Segmented', which adds an extra armor segment (but not armor value, you four get smaller segments instead of three) to the Firewerks. Both of these options feed missile swarm and result in overall more missiles being fired.

It's also worth noting that while you covered one of the hidden mechanics on the Firewerks (Missiles are the same element as the resistance on the shield), you did not cover the second one, which is that the Firewerks is self-propagating. Getting the right resistance to the party means missiles that are getting their own kills, and generating more missiles. Personal observation is that corrosive and shock will go a long way (plus corrosive resist on an armor shield is kinda wild), at least clearing the first health bar if the missiles don't outright kill.

It can also roll with no resistance on it, creating non-elemental missiles. These though, to the best of my knowledge are considered 'indirect projectiles' and do not interact with Vex. But it's hard to test that since you have to like, watch things hit and catch the right damage number, while in combat.

snippet.textDisplay:
@LegacyGamingUS   so just a few things...  The "noisy cricket" is a reference to the "Cricket" from Men in Black used by Will Smith in the first movie. Additionally it drops from ANY boss or bad4ss in the game. Just a low drop rate and "named" enemies have a higher drop chance for legendaries then bad4ss enemies do and bad4ss have higher then normal mobs and so on.

Also for the Cricket and any other AOE/Cone weapons its important to keep in mind that Vortex grenades are your Best In Slot. Another thing to note is that god-rolled PURPLES are actually currently better then all the legendaries in the game. But getting a god rolled purple is far rarer then even a legendary is because of the thousands of possible rolls they can come out with. I have a video I posted showcasing such an example of a god-rolled SMG.

Right now there is a different god roll meta for each character. Rafa for example benefits most from rate of fire and then either crit damage OR raw weapon damage depending on which type of skill mods hes using. The turret arms are the strongest option for dps for him and melee is the best for survival with the Mega-Man arm blaster being trash. So due to this the god roll for Rafa is an SMG with the extra barrel roll, ricochet, and then 2 choice perks for whichever direction you take your build.

As far as the strongest weapon in the game right now its a type of Single Shot Shotgun with an underbarrel Salvo launcher that fires 8-12x incendiary grenades doing 25,000 each. Even on VHM+1 it insta-wipes every boss in 1 hit. It is the best purple shotty in game at the moment. Like the cricket it can drop from anything just a matter of luck. But I got mine farming the Vault 1 boss on repeat since the Vault bosses appear to have the highest base drop rate for Purples making them great for farming God-Rolls.

For healing stims you can get legendary stims with as low as a 6-9 second cooldown and a 8-15k healing over time ontop of either +15% firerate, 50% ordinance cooldown, 100% skill ability cooldown reduction, 30% damage increase, 50-100% Melee Damage, 50% increased damage reduction  (all) for 8-20 seconds.  Getting one of these is a massive game changer since you can get about 70% uptime on any of those bonuses as long as you just use it on cooldown. Ontop of having endless 2K/sec healing over time.

If your a rafa player feel free to check out the video on my page to see what I mean about Rafa Firerate being meta. 
Also Rafa is probably the best character for farming because his ability can be spec'd to give crits or unlimited ammo along with dramatically increased move speed for duration and if you stack fire rate + ability duration + ability cooldown rate you can get potentially unending ult window as long as you have enemies within range making it excellent for farming. This is how mine is built in the video and I built for glass cannon and lean on 15% life steal plus a God Rolled purple shield that gives me 86% damage reduction. Legendary Rafa class mod for double overdrive bonuses is best with this and then taking the passive for double bonuses ontop if you have the points results in 4x the bonuses which gives over 90% crit chance for the crit rate one and gives you 4x any other bonuses. For example if you take the damage reduction while using your ability it can give you 99.99% damage reduction while in use as an example.

I hope this helps you guys out !
